Author::::SiberianNights
DateTime::::2016-02-18T18:50:05Z
Last summer there was good item about financial news from China on the BBC Radio 4 programme about statistics called 'More or Less'.I'll never find the link, but the message seemed to be that the financial news from China we received last year was unnecessarily alarmist and misleading, not because the Chinese were misreading their own situation, but because the figures were being converted to the incongruous western context. The Chinese capital markets were being described as if they functioned like western ones, where everything is genuinely at stake. In China, however, many of the speculators are effectively 'just pretending' and are paid to do so by the government. Huge amounts of capital cannot be lost in the same kind of way in China.



